N:log-analysis
D:Triage application, infrastructure, browser, API, CI, and general runtime logs into the first actionable failure, repeated patterns, likely scope, and next read-only checks. Use when the user shares raw log text or asks which lines matter. Not for Unity/Unreal build/editor/package logs when game-build-log-triage is the better specialist.
G:logs triage incident ci browser kubectl docker jq rg
U[6]:
  Application, API, worker, reverse-proxy, or infrastructure log triage
  CI logs where the user wants the first real blocker
  Browser console or network failures that need correlation with server logs
  JSON/text log slices that need grouping or timestamp/request-ID narrowing
  Incident review with likely root cause and next read-only checks
  Repeated errors that need a short debugging brief
S[7]{n,action}:
  1,Identify the log surface and time window
  2,Find the first actionable failure
  3,Narrow the slice before interpreting it
  4,Correlate across nearby evidence surfaces
  5,Classify the failure bucket
  6,Produce the triage brief
  7,Escalate carefully when evidence is weak
